text: Noora Komulainen (née Tamminen) (born 30 October 1990) is a Finnish professional golfer. At the 2012 Espirito Santo Trophy, Tamminen helped her team to a bronze medal finish. Komulainen turned professional in 2013 and joined the Ladies European Tour for the 2013 season. She recorded ten top-10 finishes 2013–2019, including a fourth place at the 2016 Lalla Meryem Cup, after which she rose to the top 250 in the Women's World Golf Rankings. Komulainen qualified for the 2016 Summer Olympics where she finished tied for 48th. ==Amateur wins== *2011 Mandatum Life Final *2012 Paltamo Ladies Open, Finnish Stroke Play Source: ==Team appearances== Amateur *Espirito Santo Trophy (representing Finland): 2010, 2012 ==References== ==External links== * * Category:Finnish female golfers Category:Ladies European Tour golfers Category:Olympic golfers of Finland Category:Golfers at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:Sportspeople from Tampere Category:People from Tuusula Category:1990 births Category:Living people
